Your SQL macro allows easy integration and display of data in Confluence.   We were wondering if it would be possible to add data input capabilities to this macro.  This would allow SQL insert, update and delete capabilities.  

It would be very usefult for the user to have drop down boxes to select values for embeded sql OR insert/update/delete statements.  This would really add value for simple screens and avoid the need for full blown J2EE applications.  It would be a killer app...

